Australian woman appeals against stay in Thai prison
A 21-year-old woman from Sydney, who was sentenced to 15 days in prison on Phuket Island when she falsely claimed to have been assaulted by a taxi driver, appealed the verdict and was released on bail.
Stevie Rochelle Bamford was originally indicted on June 15 by a provincial court on a false charge on Phuket Island when Thai police said the taxi driver, along with two other men who allegedly detained her, assaulted her in the early hours of Sunday, June 10.
